# PipeSay — do not break what works

Baseline tag: `v1.3-stable`. UI changes must not regress STT or startup.

## Architecture (keep)

- **Tkinter** desktop app — fast cold start; avoid CustomTkinter unless explicitly requested.
- **Soniox RT WebSocket** — accumulate `final_tokens` across messages; non-final tokens are per-response only.
- **Separate UI**: `live_frame` = streaming preview; `text_area` = finalized lines only.
- **Thread safety**: Soniox callbacks run off main thread → always marshal UI via `_ui()` / `root.after(0, ...)`.
- **Session tokens**: abort old WS before new record; ignore stale callbacks via `_rt_token`.

## Stop / record flow

- On stop: set `_finalizing_rt_token`, keep live panel updating until `on_finished`.
- Send `{"type":"finalize"}` then empty frame before closing audio stream.
- Do not rewrite the whole results widget on every partial — update `live_text` only.

## Mic / audio

- Route via acp63 @ 48kHz + `PULSE_SOURCE`; resample to 16k for Soniox.
- Always-on mic monitor for level meter; do not block window show on `pw-cli` / amixer.
- `_ensure_mic_ready()` — do not restart mic stream on every record start.

## Before merging UI work

Run: `.venv/bin/python dictation.py --test-rt-e2e` (live text must grow during stream).
